id: pm-ax7z
title: "Convert docs/examples extensions to TypeScript-first (starter-extension, policy-restricted-extension)"
description: "Honor ADR pm-2c28 for the committed docs/examples extensions, which are still authored in plain JavaScript (docs/examples/starter-extension/index.js 199L all-9-capabilities showcase + docs/examples/policy-restricted-extension/index.js). Add index.ts source authored against the SDK types, keep the compiled index.js the loader/tests import (mirror first-party packages/pm-*), and wire type-checking (add docs/examples/**/*.ts to a packages-style tsconfig include). The starter-extension test docstring already (incorrectly) claims TS authorship. Deferred from the scaffolder PR to keep that PR focused on the generator + SDK primitives + docs reframe."
type: Task
status: closed
priority: 3
tags[4]: "area:docs","area:extensions",authoring,dx
created_at: "2026-06-23T20:58:13.797Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-24T07:53:34.983Z"
author: claude-code-agent
parent: pm-ugqx
resolution: "Converted both docs/examples reference extensions (starter-extension, policy-restricted-extension) to TypeScript-first authoring: index.ts source against @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk compiled to the committed index.js entry; added tsconfig.examples.json type-check project; aligned coverage to track .ts source (compiled .js treated as runtime artifact like packages); fixed the policy output_format service signature. 100% coverage (4989 tests), all gates green, real-loader smoke verified."
expected_result: "docs/examples extensions authored TypeScript-first (index.ts source compiled to committed index.js), type-checked and coverage-tracked like first-party packages, with no runtime regression."
actual_result: Both examples converted; tsconfig.examples.json type-check project added; coverage tracks the .ts source; policy service signature corrected; 100% coverage (4989 tests) and all gates green; real-loader smoke confirmed pm starter ping and pm policy demo work.
